transcript: If you're pricing Bitcoin as if all 21 million coins are available, your math could be way off. Over the years, Bitcoin has slipped through people's fingers in every imaginable way. But the majority of potentially missing [music] coins don't have a story to tell. They're just silent. Glass Node tracks long dormant addresses with [music] no activity for over 10 years. Nearly 1 million Bitcoin are locked in them, excluding Satoshi's stash.
